    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13850#pullrequestreview-4666082905\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>LGTM, modulo one small concern below. Thanks!</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609307333,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783625498
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13850#discussion_r3554231807\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We allow <code>bxor</code> on floats and vector types and I suspect that this changed rule may break when given a float or vector of floats. Can you add a filetest for <code>bxor x, x</code> on those types if we don't already have one, and make sure that it passes?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609307335,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783625498
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13850#discussion_r3554274787\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Ah okay, here is the test.</p>\n<p>Can we also exercise floats and a vector of floats? Thanks!</p>\n</blockquote>",
