    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13850#pullrequestreview-4672719891\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks! One last question below about the new <code>all_zero</code> helper</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609482586,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783696782
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13850#discussion_r3560010290\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is it more efficient to load zeros by splatting than via loads from the constant pool?</p>\n<p>It seems like we don't have any terms in the mid-end's prelude for working with <code>ir::Constant</code>s, but they would be easy to add if necessary.</p>\n<p>But if splatting is expected to be more efficient, then we should add a comment to that effect here.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609482587,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783696782
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> myunbin submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13850#pullrequestreview-4690083508\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 609995206,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783990877
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> myunbin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13850#discussion_r3575336913\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>@fitzgen </p>\n<p>I did not use splatting for efficiency reasons, but because there is an existing rule that rewrites constant splats to <code>vconst</code> for <code>vec128</code>(I don't think there is an equivalent rule for <code>vec64</code>).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/9aca9f50ceeceb117911873bc7b86c324876b277/cranelift/codegen/src/opts/cprop.isle#L276-L287\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/9aca9f50ceeceb117911873bc7b86c324876b277/cranelift/codegen/src/opts/cprop.isle#L276-L287</a></p>\n<p>I believe adding <code>ir::Constant</code> helpers may be a better approach.</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 609995207,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783990877
    },
    {
